         <abstract>
            <p>As a progressively larger proportion of the consumer's disposable income becomes available for discretionary expenditures on comforts and luxuries, manufacturing decisions become intimately linked with marketing and selling decisions. As a result, the performance of management in the modern manufacturing corporation depends heavily on how well it formulates and executes the corporate plan. The securities analyst provides the chief executive with perhaps his most efficient channel for explaining his plan to the investing public.</p>
